<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Activity_method_arm  Entity: Activity_method  
   <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Activity_method_arm.Activity_method">
An <b>Activity_method</b>
 is a way to carry out an <express_ref linkend="activity:arm:Activity_arm.Activity"/>.
<note number="1">There may be more than one method for producing a required result
</note>

<note number="2"> 
This definition may be used to characterize a way to resolve a request for action. 
The concept of action request is dealt with in module <module_ref linkend="work_request:introduction"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Activity_method_arm  Entity: Activity_method  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.name">
is the words by which the <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/>

 is known. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Activity_method_arm  Entity: Activity_method  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.description">
is a text that provides further information about the <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/>.
 The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Activity_method_arm  Entity: Activity_method  Attribute: consequence 
   <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.consequence"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.consequence">
is a text that describes the results of application of this method. The value of this attribute need not be specified.<example>an <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/>

 is a test that consists of several steps; each may have a positive or negative result.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Activity_method_arm  Entity: Activity_method  Attribute: purpose 
   <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.purpose"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Activity_method_arm.Activity_method.purpose">
is a text that provides an informal description of the reason for the <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/>

. 
</ext_description>
